cooperate /kəʊˈɒpəˌreɪt/

(cooperating,cooperated,cooperates) BRIT also co-operate 

1. V-RECIP If you cooperate with someone, you work with them or help them for a particular purpose. You can also say that two people cooperate . 合作 

例： The U.N. had been cooperating with the State Department on a plan to find countries willing to take the refugees. 联合国和美国国务院合作，制定计划来寻找愿意接纳难民的国家。 

2. cooperation N-UNCOUNT 合作 

例： A deal with Japan could open the door to economic cooperation with East Asia. 与日本的交易可以打开与东亚经济合作的大门。 

3. V-I If you cooperate , you do what someone has asked or told you to do. 配合 

例： He agreed to cooperate with the police investigation. 他同意配合警方调查。 

4. cooperation N-UNCOUNT 协作 

例： The police underlined the importance of the public's cooperation in the hunt for the bombers. 在寻找安置炸弹的人时，警察强调了公众协作的重要性。

</div>

